headline: Hardly a Swing State When Democrats Lose Worse Than Last Time
text: LARGO, Fla. — Cliff Gephart, the co-owner of a Trump-themed coffee shop called Conservative Grounds, looked across the guns mounted on the wall, the cappuccinos in paper cups and the replica of the Oval Office he built against the back of the cafe, complete with a reproduction of the Resolute Desk. It was Tuesday, and Mr. Gephart, 50, was in a good mood.
snippet: The president’s victory in his adopted home state has Democrats once again worrying about their future electoral prospects.
